WEBVTT

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:11.519
So the core task of what we will do in

00:00:08.639 --> 00:00:14.080
this course is to teach a computer to

00:00:11.519 --> 00:00:17.680
learn a function. This function will be

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:21.119
learned from a set of examples. We start

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:25.840
with a data set D. Basically the set of

00:00:21.119 --> 00:00:30.400
input and output. These outputs are the

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:33.760
desired outputs. We want later when the

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:36.880
computer sees new access that follows

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:39.920
the same distribution as D can predict

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:43.040
this desired output. So assume just to

00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:46.239
formalize this that we have n of these

00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:47.920
examples that we can use to learn this

00:00:46.239 --> 00:00:50.879
function. So this function should be

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:53.360
flexible enough that can characterize

00:00:50.879 --> 00:00:57.120
all of these relationships that are

00:00:53.360 --> 00:01:01.039
between X and Y. So for example, a data

00:00:57.120 --> 00:01:05.040
matrix of n rows and each one of these

00:01:01.039 --> 00:01:09.280
observation or samples has the features

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:11.600
in for example a classification task. We

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.680
want to classify each one of these

00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:19.360
samples into a class zero or one. So y

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:22.240
will take a shape like a vector of n

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:25.920
dimension of zero and ones. But we can

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:30.960
also have a regression where basically f

00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:34.240
is a function from um x to a real value.

00:01:30.960 --> 00:01:37.759
So like I said, we want f to be flexible

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:40.320
enough that when later we give an x i

00:01:37.759 --> 00:01:43.439
that we never saw in the training, but

00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:46.479
we know that x i is following the same

00:01:43.439 --> 00:01:50.240
probability as uh training data, we want

00:01:46.479 --> 00:01:53.439
our flexible f to predict uh the desired

00:01:50.240 --> 00:01:56.479
output. So why this is a difficult

00:01:53.439 --> 00:01:58.719
problem? One main reason is f should be

00:01:56.479 --> 00:02:02.880
flexible like I said but at the same

00:01:58.719 --> 00:02:06.079
time we can have many f that can satisfy

00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:08.959
this condition. However we want one of

00:02:06.079 --> 00:02:12.480
them that maybe is most suited to our

00:02:08.959 --> 00:02:15.440
case or performs best in this specific

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:17.840
context. So to come up with that f

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:20.800
sometimes we need to give the algorithm

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:24.480
an inductive bias to basically go toward

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:26.560
the f the type of f that we want. In our

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:30.160
previous courses for example in linear

00:02:26.560 --> 00:02:34.640
regression we chose a linear model to be

00:02:30.160 --> 00:02:38.000
the class that our f belongs to. So this

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:41.680
type of f basically assumes the world is

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:44.000
linear and it can fail when we have a

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:46.959
complex data that is not following that

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:49.680
wall. We will call this situation a high

00:02:46.959 --> 00:02:52.959
bias situation where we are very off

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:56.400
from the real data. The model is off.

00:02:52.959 --> 00:02:59.920
The model is simple. So it will have low

00:02:56.400 --> 00:03:02.400
variance. But of course this strong bias

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:05.040
is not desirable. In deep neural

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:08.239
networks, we have a weak bias, meaning

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:10.959
that F is much more flexible. Um, this

00:03:08.239 --> 00:03:13.440
flexibility lets it learn complex

00:03:10.959 --> 00:03:16.000
patterns. But of course, this comes with

00:03:13.440 --> 00:03:19.200
a risk of overfeeding. So, we should be

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:21.599
always alert on how to deal with this.

00:03:19.200 --> 00:03:25.120
This is a case of high variance and low

00:03:21.599 --> 00:03:27.280
bias. And sometimes neural networks are

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:29.840
actually able to memorize the entire

00:03:27.280 --> 00:03:33.120
training data. and then when you deploy

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:36.159
into the test data they will perform

00:03:33.120 --> 00:03:40.560
poorly. Okay. So let's assume uh a class

00:03:36.159 --> 00:03:45.280
for our f that we want our f to to

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:48.159
follow that class. So often time we will

00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:52.000
uh parameterize this family or this

00:03:48.159 --> 00:03:54.799
class by a set of tuning parameters. So

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:58.799
W you can think of W like a tuning par

00:03:54.799 --> 00:04:01.599
and when when we have a given input this

00:03:58.799 --> 00:04:04.560
function will give us yi right the

00:04:01.599 --> 00:04:08.799
desired output. So when we have a very

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:11.760
good tuning for such function so let's

00:04:08.799 --> 00:04:15.599
call this good tuning our estimation of

00:04:11.760 --> 00:04:19.359
that W or that set of parameters. So we

00:04:15.599 --> 00:04:22.960
want to find or estimate such W that can

00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:26.080
work well to this unseen data and we

00:04:22.960 --> 00:04:28.639
want to be able to assign a label that

00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:32.400
is an accurate label or good enough

00:04:28.639 --> 00:04:35.280
label that is close to what we want. So

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:37.600
we want to learn this W. Then the

00:04:35.280 --> 00:04:41.280
problem of learning here is finding or

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:43.919
estimating this W's and then we want

00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:47.360
such function to be able to do inference

00:04:43.919 --> 00:04:50.560
for us. So inference is prediction of

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:53.520
this label in the unseen data. So these

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:56.560
are the lingos that we are going to use.

00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:59.360
So with that I'm going to focus on the

00:04:56.560 --> 00:05:02.160
linear regression. Just to do a recap

00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:04.479
during this I will call some of these

00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:07.280
concepts that we learned there and we

00:05:04.479 --> 00:05:09.440
are going to use later in during the

00:05:07.280 --> 00:05:12.000
course.

00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:14.960
So in linear regression we assume a

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:17.440
linear relationship between y and x. So

00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:20.479
we wrote this linear relationship like

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:24.479
this. So basically what this gives us is

00:05:20.479 --> 00:05:27.280
a hyper plane in the space of x. And for

00:05:24.479 --> 00:05:29.680
example in the case of classification

00:05:27.280 --> 00:05:32.960
for a X that is two-dimensional nice

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:35.919
ukidian uh two-dimensional space this

00:05:32.960 --> 00:05:38.400
will give us a linear plane that

00:05:35.919 --> 00:05:41.199
basically separate the space in two

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:45.039
part. So for example maybe the positive

00:05:41.199 --> 00:05:48.800
part can be from this part. Like I said

00:05:45.039 --> 00:05:52.800
the uh the equation that determines this

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:56.720
decision boundary is this linear uh

00:05:52.800 --> 00:06:01.680
equation. So what we want to completely

00:05:56.720 --> 00:06:04.319
define the cyerspace is the weights and

