00:40:14.560 --> 00:40:19.920
The main reason and the main problem

00:40:16.400 --> 00:40:24.320
with uh this SGDs like we discussed in

00:40:19.920 --> 00:40:28.000
the uh choice of batch size they can

00:40:24.320 --> 00:40:30.400
oscillate in narrow valleys and they can

00:40:28.000 --> 00:40:32.960
progress slowly because the only thing

00:40:30.400 --> 00:40:36.560
that they have to control their

00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:40.720
conversions is this alpha here. So we

00:40:36.560 --> 00:40:44.000
can add more options to improve this.

00:40:40.720 --> 00:40:47.680
One options is adding momentum. By

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:53.040
adding momentum I mean so instead of the

00:40:47.680 --> 00:40:56.880
initial W's we uh update the momentum

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:59.359
based on the gradient.

00:40:56.880 --> 00:41:03.760
So this is known known as velocity

00:40:59.359 --> 00:41:05.680
update which then will uh do the update

00:41:03.760 --> 00:41:08.640
on the parameters.

00:41:05.680 --> 00:41:12.079
Here we call beta uh momentum

00:41:08.640 --> 00:41:16.720
coefficient that can take values uh

00:41:12.079 --> 00:41:22.000
typically between 0.9 and 99.

00:41:16.720 --> 00:41:27.599
So the the intuition for u this momentum

00:41:22.000 --> 00:41:30.960
based uh SGD is basically um imagine

00:41:27.599 --> 00:41:33.760
like a ball rolling downhill.

00:41:30.960 --> 00:41:36.240
it builds up speed in consistent

00:41:33.760 --> 00:41:39.200
directions and rolls through small

00:41:36.240 --> 00:41:43.520
bumps. So this way it will be more

00:41:39.200 --> 00:41:46.240
consistent and uh may have the more and

00:41:43.520 --> 00:41:49.280
faster uh desirable conversions

00:41:46.240 --> 00:41:53.040
properties. One variation of u this

00:41:49.280 --> 00:41:58.440
modern SGD algorithm that we will use a

00:41:53.040 --> 00:41:58.440
lot during the course is known as ADA.

00:41:58.800 --> 00:42:05.359
The ATOM stands for adaptive moment

00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:07.839
estimation and it combines momentum with

00:42:05.359 --> 00:42:10.880
adaptive learning rates for each one of

00:42:07.839 --> 00:42:13.680
these parameters. Like I said, momentum

00:42:10.880 --> 00:42:16.319
helps SGD to navigate this narrow

00:42:13.680 --> 00:42:19.119
valleys basically escape from them

00:42:16.319 --> 00:42:24.000
efficiently by accumulating velocity in

00:42:19.119 --> 00:42:26.400
cons consistent directions. In this case

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:29.280
basically but what we mean by momentum

00:42:26.400 --> 00:42:31.200
is uh the algorithm accumulate this past

00:42:29.280 --> 00:42:34.240
gradients

00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:36.640
and adaptive rates uh basically scale

00:42:34.240 --> 00:42:40.839
the learning rate for each parameter

00:42:36.640 --> 00:42:40.839
based on gradient history.

00:42:41.200 --> 00:42:48.400
There is a bias correction where uh

00:42:45.040 --> 00:42:51.359
accounts for initialization bias. So as

00:42:48.400 --> 00:42:54.240
you will see Adam will be our go-to

00:42:51.359 --> 00:42:58.960
option most of the time uh because of

00:42:54.240 --> 00:43:02.800
all of these properties we may uh employ

00:42:58.960 --> 00:43:04.560
learning rate scheduulers that basically

00:43:02.800 --> 00:43:11.040
uh control

00:43:04.560 --> 00:43:14.079
this uh step sizes and reduce um them

00:43:11.040 --> 00:43:17.920
for more fine tuning over the training.

00:43:14.079 --> 00:43:21.760
So if you want to give a summary uh to

00:43:17.920 --> 00:43:24.880
this section, we start from some W. Most

00:43:21.760 --> 00:43:28.079
of the time we start from random uh

00:43:24.880 --> 00:43:31.839
